Member Enumeration Documentation

enum Cbs::SerialNumber::GeographicalScope
 

Enumerator:
CellWideImmediate  only cell wide by default direkt display (which means that any CBS message if received in the next cell is regarded as "new")
PlmnWideNormal  PLMN wide (which means that the Message Code and/or Update Number must change in the next cell for the CBS message to be "new")
LocationAreaWideNormal  Location area wide (in GSM) by default display under user interaction (which means that a CBS message with the same Message Code and Update Number may or may not be "new" in the next cell according to whether the next cell is in the same Location Area as the current cell) The corresponding scpoe in UMTS is called service area!
CellWideNormal  only cell wide by default display under user interaction (which means that any CBS message if received in the next cell is regarded as "new")
InvalidScope
